            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any ocean<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The giant squid is a legendary beast capable of feeding on humans with ease. Hunger has been known to drive these normally deep-dwelling creatures up to the ocean surface where anything they encounter is potential prey. A giant squid is 45 feet long and weighs 1,500 pounds."
        }
    ],
